quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  69,35,"“So he does not have any friend here this day.”"
  69,36,"“Nor any food except the pus discharged from the people of hell.”"
  69,37,"“Which none except the guilty shall eat.”"
  69,38,"So by oath of the things you see."
  69,39,"And by oath of those you do not see."
  69,40,"This Qur’an is the speech of Allah with a gracious Noble Messenger."
  69,41,"And it is not the speech of a poet; how little do you believe!"
  69,42,"Nor is it the speech of a soothsayer; how little do you ponder!"
  69,43,"Sent down by the Lord Of The Creation."
  69,44,"And had he fabricated just one matter upon Us –"
  69,45,"We would have definitely taken revenge from him."
  69,46,"Then would have cut off his heart’s artery."
  69,47,"Then none among you would be his saviour."
  69,48,"And indeed this Qur’an is an advice for the pious."
  69,49,"And indeed We know that some among you are deniers."
  69,50,"And indeed it is a despair for the disbelievers."
  69,51,"And indeed it is a certain Truth."
  69,52,"Therefore (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him), proclaim the purity of your Lord, the Greatest."
  70,1,"A requester seeks the punishment that will take place –"
  70,2,"- Upon the disbelievers – the punishment that none can avert."
  70,3,"From Allah, the Lord of all pinnacles."
  70,4,"The angels and Jibreel, ascend towards Him – the punishment will befall on a day which spans fifty thousand years."
  70,5,"Therefore patiently endure, in the best manner (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him)."
  70,6,"They deem it to be remote."
  70,7,"Whereas We see it impending."
  70,8,"The day when the sky will be like molten silver."
  70,9,"And the hills will be light as wool."
  70,10,"And no friend will ask concerning his friend."
